### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

common, core

### Description

With the new control flow template discriminate unions type safety works easily and perfectly.
Considering a model:
```ts
test: {type: 'a', value: number} | {type: 'b', name: string} = {type: 'a', value: 8};
```
And template:
```html
@if (test.type === 'a') {
  {{test.value}}
} @else if (test.type === 'b') {
  {{test.name}}
} @else {
  ...
}
```
Everything works great.
But when using signals I can't seem to make it work as expected (won't compile):
Model:
```ts
test = signal<{type: 'a', value: number} | {type: 'b', name: string}>({type: 'a', value: 8});
```
And template:
```html
@if (test().type === 'a') {
  {{test().value}}
} @else if (test().type === 'b') {
  {{test().name}}
} @else {
  ...
}
```

### Proposed solution

Maybe allow aliasing the result? Automatic variables? Not sure what's the best way to fix that.

### Alternatives considered

1. Create many small signals for every case. Effectively duplicating the if else logic in computed too.
2. Use `@if as` or some other structural directive to alias the signal value as template variable and use it instead.

